> Folks, for what it's worth:
>
> I recently bought a gorgeous Volvo 765 with nary a problem but a sagging
> headliner.  I took it to a local
> Headliners Plus! guy, and was consequently so impressed with his work and
> rates, I went home, drove
> my 78 Westy back to him, and asked what he could do about that godforsaken
> mildew stain on the
> "fuzzy" crap that lines the inside of the poptop. (I had, by that point,
> spent egregious amounts of money
> on surely every commercially-available product... and nearly killed myself
> in the process a number of times:
> fumes tend to congregate up there!)
>
> Well, he takes a gander, and in the end, for a mere $250, he installed a
> "marine-grade" headliner, a nice
> comfy kinda stuff, PADDED mind you, and (here's the kicker) applied 3/4"
oak
> strips all the way around
> the inside of the poptop - to which he re-stapled the canvas (which was
> sagging on one side) and screwed
> them into the fiberglass.
>
> It looks incredible - and is surely the one-thing-I-didn't-do-myself of
> which I am the proudest! I highly
> encourage other folks to investigate similar options, if $250 is
reasonable
> for them.
>
> Cheers!
